							<div class="sponsored-riders-datasheet__content">
								<h2>From Townsville to the Top Step: The Jack Miller Story</h2>
								<p>
									Jack Miller grew up in Townsville, Queensland, honing his skills on dirt bikes from age eight. He raced across Australia and Europe, securing the 2011 German 125cc IDM title. 
								</p><p>
									Turning pro in MotoGP in 2015 with Honda, he shocked the paddock by winning the 2016 Dutch TT—a rare satellite victory.His career soared after moving to Ducati’s factory outfit in 2021, where he notched two wins (Jerez and Le Mans) and finished a career-best 4th in the championship. 
								</p><p>
									Known for his nerves of steel, Miller continued to rack up podiums and claimed his fourth premier-class win at the 2022 Japanese GP.In 2023 he joined Red Bull KTM Factory Racing, then in 2025 moved to Prima Pramac Yamaha. He’s also set to ride in the prestigious Suzuka 8 Hours for Yamaha's factory team. An Alpinestars athlete throughout, Jack trusts the brand’s gear for peak performance and protection.
								</p>
							</div>
